West Nile Virus-positive Crows Detected in New Jersey
-----------------------------------------------------
2 crows have tested positive for West Nile virus in New Jersey. The 2 dead
crows were turned in for testing on 30 Apr 2001 from Bergen County (Upper
Saddle River) and on 1 May 2001 [2 May 2001 in other reports. - Mod from
Middlesex County (Edison Township). Both these counties showed high crow
mortality last year. It should be noted that American and Fish Crows are
now sitting on eggs in their nests and have been doing so since early
April. This means that they are NOT using communal roosts and are not
likely to have traveled far from their territory.
--
Lisa Reed
Dept Entomology,
Rutgers University,
NJ USA
<lreed@RCI.RUTGERS.EDU>
